OL,6,FThis was down 15% from the end of
OL,7,FDecember, when the total was 38,079,
OL,8,Fand 6% lower than the 34,530 at the
OL,9,Fsame point a year earlier.
OL,11,FFigures on those staying in hotels
OL,12,Fdate back to December 2022 and showed
OL,13,Fnumbers hit a peak at the end of
OL,14,FSeptember 2023, when there were 56,042
OL,15,Fasylum seekers in hotels. Data is not
OL,16,Freleased on the number of hotels in
OL,17,Fuse, but it is thought there were more
OL,18,Fthan 400 asylum hotels open in summer
OL,19,F2023.
